        }
      },
      {
        "heading": "The Nile Monitor",
        "content": "<h3>Scientific Name: <em>Varanus niloticus</em></h3><p>This large, agile lizard is commonly found near rivers and lakes. Known for its impressive swimming ability, the Nile Monitor plays a key role in controlling pest populations but is often hunted for its skin.</p>",
        "image": {
          "source": "https://www.placeholderimage.online/placeholder/800/600/f3f4f6/1f2937?font=Lato.svg/nile-monitor-lizard.jpg",
          "caption": "The Nile Monitor, a large and agile lizard, plays a crucial role in controlling pest populations in Nigeria."
        }
      },
      {
        "heading": "The West African Crocodile",
        "content": "<h3>Scientific Name: <em>Crocodylus suchus</em></h3><p>Once considered the same species as the Nile Crocodile, the West African Crocodile inhabits freshwater habitats across Nigeria. It is a keystone species, crucial for maintaining the balance of aquatic ecosystems.</p>",
