          "source": "https://www.placeholderimage.online/placeholder/800/600/f3f4f6/1f2937?font=Lato.svg/west-african-crocodile.jpg",
          "caption": "The West African Crocodile, a keystone species in Nigeria's freshwater ecosystems."
        }
      },
      {
        "heading": "The Dwarf Crocodile",
        "content": "<h3>Scientific Name: <em>Osteolaemus tetraspis</em></h3><p>This small and secretive crocodile is primarily found in the rainforests of southern Nigeria. It is critically endangered due to habitat loss and hunting for bushmeat.</p>",
        "image": {
          "source": "https://www.placeholderimage.online/placeholder/800/600/f3f4f6/1f2937?font=Lato.svg/dwarf-crocodile-endangered.jpg",
          "caption": "The critically endangered Dwarf Crocodile, found in the rainforests of southern Nigeria."
